<graph edgedefault="undirected"><node id="WAWF">
  <data key="d0">WAWF</data>
  <data key="d1">technology</data>
  <data key="d2">WAWF is a system for citing information per individual task order and contacting its helpdesk at 866-618-5988 for assistance.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-3b65cbb31e854658ff984a34247acde1</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759711344</data>
</node>
<node id="N6945025R0003">
  <data key="d0">N6945025R0003</data>
  <data key="d1">document</data>
  <data key="d2">N6945025R0003 is the solicitation and resulting contract number referenced throughout the document.&lt;SEP&gt;This is the solicitation or contract number referenced in various clauses, attachments, and file names throughout the document.&lt;SEP&gt;N6945025R0003 is the contract identifier for a performance-based contract providing base operations support services.&lt;SEP&gt;N6945025R0003 is the solicitation number referenced throughout the document sections.&lt;SEP&gt;This is the solicitation number for the Mayport BOS procurement.&lt;SEP&gt;N6945025R0003 is the contract or solicitation number referenced throughout the document.&lt;SEP&gt;N6945025R0003 is the contract identifier appearing on multiple pages of the document, including sections on contract clauses.&lt;SEP&gt;The identifier for the solicitation or contract, referenced in the context of evaluation preferences and rerepresentations.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-516b1e6efecfd543f141d1e1135ec455&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-3b65cbb31e854658ff984a34247acde1&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-6266f048b10bdb8222f03b8f5e597d7e&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-4bcb91b404a9ca74c18944c1ba7f80a2&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-96e30762ee04dbe2af303802d3d2a936&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-3e097b0647fa14f34c4ff76380ed4beb&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-bafeb026eba657c5147474a89dc0e6f9&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-5874f638e9cb9ecd09e53d314b07e103</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759711344</data>
</node>
<node id="Section H">
  <data key="d0">Section H</data>
  <data key="d1">section</data>
  <data key="d2">Section H outlines special contract requirements including historical resources, FedMall usage, ordering, and construction work.&lt;SEP&gt;Section H contains the special requirement on consequences of the Contractor's failure to perform required services, used for calculating liquidated damages.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-3b65cbb31e854658ff984a34247acde1&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-96e30762ee04dbe2af303802d3d2a936</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759711344</data>
</node>
<node id="Historical And Archaeological Resources">
  <data key="d0">Historical And Archaeological Resources</data>
  <data key="d1">section</data>
  <data key="d2">Historical And Archaeological Resources is Section H.1 requiring protection and reporting of discovered items to the Contracting Officer.&lt;SEP&gt;Historical And Archaeological Resources must be protected in-place, reported immediately to the Contracting Officer if discovered, with work stopped in the area until directed to resume; the Government retains ownership.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-3b65cbb31e854658ff984a34247acde1&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-5874f638e9cb9ecd09e53d314b07e103</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759711344</data>
</node>
<node id="FedMall">
  <data key="d0">FedMall</data>
  <data key="d1">technology</data>
  <data key="d2">FedMall is a U.S. Government-owned web-based ordering system for DoD and Federal activities to search and order goods and services via GCPC.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-3b65cbb31e854658ff984a34247acde1</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759711344</data>
</node>
<node id="Governmentwide Commercial Purchase Card Program">
  <data key="d0">Governmentwide Commercial Purchase Card Program</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Governmentwide Commercial Purchase Card Program is a method for authorized Government personnel to order work directly through FedMall at pre-priced rates.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-3b65cbb31e854658ff984a34247acde1</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759711344</data>
</node>
<node id="Department Of Defense">
  <data key="d0">Department Of Defense</data>
  <data key="d1">organization</data>
  <data key="d2">Department Of Defense operates FedMall and establishes the External Certification Authority program for secure communications.&lt;SEP&gt;Department Of Defense is the entity that owns and operates Fedmall and establishes programs like External Certification Authority for secure contractor interactions.&lt;SEP&gt;The Department of Defense (DoD) is referenced in multiple DFARS clauses concerning compensation of former officials, fraud convictions, whistleblower rights, inspector general, and assessment requirements.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-3b65cbb31e854658ff984a34247acde1&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-5874f638e9cb9ecd09e53d314b07e103&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-96e30762ee04dbe2af303802d3d2a936</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759711344</data>
</node>
<node id="Defense Logistics Agency">
  <data key="d0">Defense Logistics Agency</data>
  <data key="d1">organization</data>
  <data key="d2">Defense Logistics Agency provides the website for FedMall supplier registration.&lt;SEP&gt;The Defense Logistics Agency is one of the sources from which the required supplies are available.&lt;SEP&gt;The DLA provides mandatory supplies like trash liners and toilet paper for the contract.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-3b65cbb31e854658ff984a34247acde1&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-6266f048b10bdb8222f03b8f5e597d7e&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-4bcb91b404a9ca74c18944c1ba7f80a2</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759711344</data>
</node>
<node id="External Certification Authority">
  <data key="d0">External Certification Authority</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">External Certification Authority is a DoD program issuing approved certificates to contractors for secure communication and authentication to DoD systems.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-3b65cbb31e854658ff984a34247acde1</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759711344</data>
</node>
<node id="Contracting Officer">
  <data key="d0">Contracting Officer</data>
  <data key="d1">person</data>
  <data key="d2">Contracting Officer directs resumption of work after discoveries, receives notifications, and approves identifications and substitutions.&lt;SEP&gt;The official who exercises options by written notice, requires rerepresentations, establishes unilateral rates if uncertified, and provides clause texts upon request.&lt;SEP&gt;The Contracting Officer specifies time limits for negotiating subcontracting plans and determines eligibility for contract award.&lt;SEP&gt;The Contracting Officer deems appropriate methodologies for price evaluation consistent with FAR 15.404-1.&lt;SEP&gt;Contracting Officer is the representative who determines the time for the pre-performance conference and discusses work scheduling and administration with the contractor.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-3b65cbb31e854658ff984a34247acde1&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-9775b66c35e6cfe40c05dbf72803d6cd&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-729293c3f8703afb2cb5e31cb6ff90dd&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-bafeb026eba657c5147474a89dc0e6f9&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-ac133babc8ecde7c6f7014a40f53ce13</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759711344</data>
</node>
<node id="Contractor">
  <data key="d0">Contractor</data>
  <data key="d1">organization</data>
  <data key="d2">Contractor must register with FedMall, upload catalogs, accept GCPC orders, track quantities, and comply with various requirements including bonding and quality control.&lt;SEP&gt;The entity required to perform services, complete orders, rerepresent status, certify costs, and comply with contract terms and clauses.&lt;SEP&gt;The Contractor performs required services under the contract and is liable for liquidated damages calculated in accordance with Section H for failure to perform.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-bafeb026eba657c5147474a89dc0e6f9&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-3b65cbb31e854658ff984a34247acde1&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-96e30762ee04dbe2af303802d3d2a936</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759711344</data>
</node>
<node id="ELIN">
  <data key="d0">ELIN</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">ELIN refers to Equipment Line Item Numbers used for ordering via FedMall, including items like Temporary HVAC units and services.&lt;SEP&gt;ELIN stands for Exhibit Line Item Number, used to identify and total pricing for services in the contract's option line items, with specific ranges referenced from Attachment J-0200000-17.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-3e097b0647fa14f34c4ff76380ed4beb&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-3b65cbb31e854658ff984a34247acde1</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759711344</data>
</node>
<node id="Blount Island">
  <data key="d0">Blount Island</data>
  <data key="d1">location</data>
  <data key="d2">Blount Island is referenced in ELIN X718 for shoreline cleanup services.&lt;SEP&gt;Blount Island is a site associated with Marine Corps Support Facility (MCSF-BI), including site visits, facility inventories, and specific systems like auxiliary generators and cathodic protection.&lt;SEP&gt;Blount Island is referenced in the shoreline cleanup plan and map for MCSF-BI grounds maintenance.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-516b1e6efecfd543f141d1e1135ec455&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-9e005e41da996ebb18d009a4f87b0e3c&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-3b65cbb31e854658ff984a34247acde1</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759711344</data>
</node>
<node id="Ordering">
  <data key="d0">Ordering</data>
  <data key="d1">section</data>
  <data key="d2">Ordering is Section H.3 authorizing oral, facsimile, and electronic commerce methods for issuing delivery or task orders per FAR 52.216-18.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-3b65cbb31e854658ff984a34247acde1</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759711344</data>
</node>
<node id="Order Limitations">
  <data key="d0">Order Limitations</data>
  <data key="d1">section</data>
  <data key="d2">Order Limitations is Section H.4 incorporating FAR 52.216-19, not applicable to recurring work, FedMall orders, or GCPC Program.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-3b65cbb31e854658ff984a34247acde1</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759711344</data>
</node>
<node id="Construction Work">
  <data key="d0">Construction Work</data>
  <data key="d1">section</data>
  <data key="d2">Construction Work is Section H.5 specifying applicability of labor standards and various FAR clauses to construction efforts under the contract.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-3b65cbb31e854658ff984a34247acde1</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759711344</data>
</node>
<node id="Commencement Prosecution And Completion Of Work">
  <data key="d0">Commencement Prosecution And Completion Of Work</data>
  <data key="d1">section</data>
  <data key="d2">Commencement Prosecution And Completion Of Work is Section H.6 incorporating FAR 52.211-10 for task order performance periods.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-3b65cbb31e854658ff984a34247acde1</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759711344</data>
</node>
<node id="DFARS 211.106">
  <data key="d0">DFARS 211.106</data>
  <data key="d1">clause</data>
  <data key="d2">DFARS 211.106 requires Contractor employees to display identification as approved by the Contracting Officer.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-3b65cbb31e854658ff984a34247acde1</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759711344</data>
</node>
<node id="Schedule Of Deductions">
  <data key="d0">Schedule Of Deductions</data>
  <data key="d1">section</data>
  <data key="d2">Schedule Of Deductions is Section H.8 using unit prices for deductions under FAR 52.246-4.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-3b65cbb31e854658ff984a34247acde1</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759711344</data>
</node>
<node id="Government Property">
  <data key="d0">Government Property</data>
  <data key="d1">section</data>
  <data key="d2">Government Property is Section H.9 stating no Government property is included, but facilities and utilities are available in as-is condition.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-3b65cbb31e854658ff984a34247acde1</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759711344</data>
</node>
<node id="Authority">
  <data key="d0">Authority</data>
  <data key="d1">section</data>
  <data key="d2">Authority is Section H.10 limiting binding actions to the Contracting Officer only.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-3b65cbb31e854658ff984a34247acde1</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759711344</data>
</node>
<node id="Substitutions Of Key Personnel">
  <data key="d0">Substitutions Of Key Personnel</data>
  <data key="d1">section</data>
  <data key="d2">Substitutions Of Key Personnel is Section H.11 requiring resumes and comparable qualifications for approvals by the Contracting Officer.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-3b65cbb31e854658ff984a34247acde1</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759711344</data>
</node>
<node id="Consequences Of Contractor's Failure To Perform Required Services">
  <data key="d0">Consequences Of Contractor's Failure To Perform Required Services</data>
  <data key="d1">section</data>
  <data key="d2">Consequences Of Contractor's Failure To Perform Required Services is Section H.12 detailing inspection, re-performance, withholdings, and liquidated damages.&lt;SEP&gt;This special requirement in Section H outlines the consequences, including liquidated damages, for the Contractor's nonperformance or unsatisfactory performance of required services.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-3b65cbb31e854658ff984a34247acde1&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-96e30762ee04dbe2af303802d3d2a936</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759711344</data>
</node>
<node id="Estimating Nonperformed Work">
  <data key="d0">Estimating Nonperformed Work</data>
  <data key="d1">section</data>
  <data key="d2">Estimating Nonperformed Work is Section H.13 using methods to determine costs for unsatisfactory work and calculating liquidated damages.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-3b65cbb31e854658ff984a34247acde1</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759711344</data>
</node>
<node id="Section I">
  <data key="d0">Section I</data>
  <data key="d1">section</data>
  <data key="d2">Section I lists Contract Clauses incorporated by reference, including various FAR clauses.&lt;SEP&gt;Section I contains contract clauses, including clause 52.232-8 for discounts for prompt payment.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-f8cbd3bc2ef4445a2ce77064100a7a3e&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-3b65cbb31e854658ff984a34247acde1</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759711344</data>
</node>
<node id="FAR 52.216-18">
  <data key="d0">FAR 52.216-18</data>
  <data key="d1">clause</data>
  <data key="d2">FAR 52.216-18 is the Ordering clause authorizing additional methods for task orders.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-3b65cbb31e854658ff984a34247acde1</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759711344</data>
</node>
<node id="FAR 52.216-19">
  <data key="d0">FAR 52.216-19</data>
  <data key="d1">clause</data>
  <data key="d2">FAR 52.216-19 is the Order Limitations clause incorporated but not applicable to certain programs.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-3b65cbb31e854658ff984a34247acde1</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759711344</data>
</node>
<node id="FAR 52.211-12">
  <data key="d0">FAR 52.211-12</data>
  <data key="d1">clause</data>
  <data key="d2">FAR 52.211-12 is Liquidated Damages for Construction applicable to construction work.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-3b65cbb31e854658ff984a34247acde1</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759711344</data>
</node>
<node id="FAR 52.222-6">
  <data key="d0">FAR 52.222-6</data>
  <data key="d1">clause</data>
  <data key="d2">FAR 52.222-6 is Construction Wage Rate Requirements applicable to construction efforts.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-3b65cbb31e854658ff984a34247acde1</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759711344</data>
</node>
<node id="FAR 52.228-15">
  <data key="d0">FAR 52.228-15</data>
  <data key="d1">clause</data>
  <data key="d2">FAR 52.228-15 is Performance and Payment Bonds for Construction required per Miller Act.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-3b65cbb31e854658ff984a34247acde1</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759711344</data>
</node>
<node id="FAR 52.246-4">
  <data key="d0">FAR 52.246-4</data>
  <data key="d1">clause</data>
  <data key="d2">FAR 52.246-4 is Inspection of Services - Fixed-Price used for assessing performance and deductions.&lt;SEP&gt;FAR 52.246-4 is the clause titled Inspection of Services-Fixed-Price, effective August 1996, incorporated by reference in Section E.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-3e097b0647fa14f34c4ff76380ed4beb&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-3b65cbb31e854658ff984a34247acde1</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759711344</data>
</node>
<node id="FAR 52.211-11">
  <data key="d0">FAR 52.211-11</data>
  <data key="d1">clause</data>
  <data key="d2">FAR 52.211-11 is Liquidated Damages for Supplies, Services, or Research and Development applicable to non-performed work.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-3b65cbb31e854658ff984a34247acde1</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759711344</data>
</node>
<node id="FAR 52.249-8">
  <data key="d0">FAR 52.249-8</data>
  <data key="d1">clause</data>
  <data key="d2">FAR 52.249-8 is Default for Fixed-Price Supply and Service for termination rights.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-3b65cbb31e854658ff984a34247acde1</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759711344</data>
</node>
<node id="DD 1155">
  <data key="d0">DD 1155</data>
  <data key="d1">document</data>
  <data key="d2">DD 1155 is a form used for orders that the Contractor must track and report quantities from.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-3b65cbb31e854658ff984a34247acde1</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759711344</data>
</node>
<node id="PGP Personal Software">
  <data key="d0">PGP Personal Software</data>
  <data key="d1">technology</data>
  <data key="d2">PGP Personal Software is required for decrypting FedMall order notifications, or a comparable solution.&lt;SEP&gt;PGP Personal Software is a tool required for contractors to decrypt 128-bit encrypted email notifications from Fedmall orders.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-3b65cbb31e854658ff984a34247acde1&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-5874f638e9cb9ecd09e53d314b07e103</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759711344</data>
</node>
<node id="Miller Act">
  <data key="d0">Miller Act</data>
  <data key="d1">requirement</data>
  <data key="d2">Miller Act mandates performance and payment bonds for construction task orders.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-3b65cbb31e854658ff984a34247acde1</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759711344</data>
</node>
<node id="Government">
  <data key="d0">Government</data>
  <data key="d1">organization</data>
  <data key="d2">The party that may require performance, exercise options, extend terms, evaluate offers with preferences, and limit obligations in incrementally funded items.&lt;SEP&gt;The Government estimates the Contractor's overhead and profit rates, material costs if applicable, and receives liquidated damages to compensate for administrative costs and expenses from nonperformed or unsatisfactory performance.&lt;SEP&gt;Government evaluates offeror proposals on safety commitment, past performance, and other factors, reserves rights to review information sources, negotiate, and award contracts based on best value.&lt;SEP&gt;Government retains ownership and control over historical and archaeological resources, inspects contractor performance, provides facilities and utilities in as-is condition, and assesses remedies for non-performance.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-bafeb026eba657c5147474a89dc0e6f9&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-6277b393cb9cf1d4f0f247c35b0fffa1&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-3b65cbb31e854658ff984a34247acde1&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-96e30762ee04dbe2af303802d3d2a936</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759711344</data>
</node>
<node id="Section B">
  <data key="d0">Section B</data>
  <data key="d1">section</data>
  <data key="d2">Section B outlines supplies or services, pricing of contract line items, maximum not-to-exceed values, minimum guarantees, and unit price adjustments for the Base Operations Support contract.&lt;SEP&gt;Section B contains pricing information submitted within the proposal, evaluated for inconsistencies with Section J ELIN attachment.&lt;SEP&gt;Section B contains the pricing schedule and requires completion for proposal submission.&lt;SEP&gt;Section B contains the schedule of supplies and services with pre-priced line item quantities supported by ELINs in Section J.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-f8cbd3bc2ef4445a2ce77064100a7a3e&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-3b65cbb31e854658ff984a34247acde1&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-9775b66c35e6cfe40c05dbf72803d6cd&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-ac133babc8ecde7c6f7014a40f53ce13</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759711344</data>
</node>
<node id="Section C">
  <data key="d0">Section C</data>
  <data key="d1">section</data>
  <data key="d2">Section C specifies the places of performance for the work under the solicitation and resulting contract.&lt;SEP&gt;Section C describes specifications and the statement of work for the performance-based contract, with files provided as an attachment on SAM.gov.&lt;SEP&gt;Section C identifies the key personnel required for the contract.&lt;SEP&gt;Section C of Annex 17 Transportation outlines maintenance and repair requirements, limits of liability, and allowable downtime standards for transportation equipment.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-3e097b0647fa14f34c4ff76380ed4beb&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-3b65cbb31e854658ff984a34247acde1&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-729293c3f8703afb2cb5e31cb6ff90dd&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-b1019473eb9ce96e37dbd7a39cfdf02d</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759711344</data>
</node>
<node id="Section F">
  <data key="d0">Section F</data>
  <data key="d1">section</data>
  <data key="d2">Section F covers deliveries or performance, including location, contract term, transition period, pre-performance conference, and deliverables.&lt;SEP&gt;Section F specifies requirements for notifying the Contracting Officer of catalog uploads and performance periods.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-3b65cbb31e854658ff984a34247acde1&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-729293c3f8703afb2cb5e31cb6ff90dd</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759711344</data>
</node>
<node id="Section J">
  <data key="d0">Section J</data>
  <data key="d1">section</data>
  <data key="d2">Section J includes the ELIN Pricing Attachment that must be completed for pricing data submission.&lt;SEP&gt;Section J lists attachments, documents, exhibits, and other attachments, including the ELINs spreadsheet in Attachment J-0200000-17.&lt;SEP&gt;Section J provides ELINs supporting the pre-priced line items in Section B for ordering via FedMall.&lt;SEP&gt;Section J describes the systems approach for maintaining functioning systems, including all interlocked ancillary parts and components.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-f8cbd3bc2ef4445a2ce77064100a7a3e&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-3b65cbb31e854658ff984a34247acde1&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-9775b66c35e6cfe40c05dbf72803d6cd&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-b1019473eb9ce96e37dbd7a39cfdf02d</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759711344</data>
</node>
<node id="Key Personnel">
  <data key="d0">Key Personnel</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Key Personnel are individuals identified in Section C whose substitutions require Contracting Officer approval and comparable qualifications.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-3b65cbb31e854658ff984a34247acde1</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759711344</data>
</node>
<node id="Watchstanding Services">
  <data key="d0">Watchstanding Services</data>
  <data key="d1">requirement</data>
  <data key="d2">Watchstanding Services require the Contractor to provide qualified personnel continuously, with withholdings and liquidated damages for unmanned posts exceeding 10 minutes.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-3b65cbb31e854658ff984a34247acde1</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759711344</data>
</node>
