<node id="Small Business">
  <data key="d0">Small Business</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Small Business is a category with a 40% subcontracting target in NAVFAC's command-wide goals.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-6266f048b10bdb8222f03b8f5e597d7e</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759711345</data>
</node>
<node id="Small Disadvantaged Business">
  <data key="d0">Small Disadvantaged Business</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Small Disadvantaged Business is a category with a 5% subcontracting target in NAVFAC's command-wide goals.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-6266f048b10bdb8222f03b8f5e597d7e</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759711345</data>
</node>
<node id="HUBZone Small Business">
  <data key="d0">HUBZone Small Business</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">HUBZone Small Business is a category with a 3% subcontracting target in NAVFAC's command-wide goals.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-6266f048b10bdb8222f03b8f5e597d7e</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759711345</data>
</node>
<node id="Woman-Owned Small Business">
  <data key="d0">Woman-Owned Small Business</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Woman-Owned Small Business is a category with a 9% subcontracting target in NAVFAC's command-wide goals.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-6266f048b10bdb8222f03b8f5e597d7e</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759711345</data>
</node>
<node id="Service-Disabled Veteran-Owned Small Business">
  <data key="d0">Service-Disabled Veteran-Owned Small Business</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Service-Disabled Veteran-Owned Small Business is a category with a 5% subcontracting target in NAVFAC's command-wide goals.&lt;SEP&gt;Service-Disabled Veteran-Owned Small Business is referenced in clause 52.204-8 for set-asides.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-9e005e41da996ebb18d009a4f87b0e3c&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-6266f048b10bdb8222f03b8f5e597d7e</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759711345</data>
</node>
<node id="Systems Approach">
  <data key="d0">Systems Approach</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Systems Approach is a method that maintains systems including all mechanically and electrically interlocked ancillary parts, equipment, and components forming a functioning system such as fire protection, HVAC, and utility systems.&lt;SEP&gt;Systems Approach requires maintenance of entire systems including all interlocked ancillary parts and components, with understanding demonstrated for applicable annexes and spec items.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-ac133babc8ecde7c6f7014a40f53ce13&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-b1019473eb9ce96e37dbd7a39cfdf02d</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759711345</data>
</node>
<node id="Limits of Liability">
  <data key="d0">Limits of Liability</data>
  <data key="d1">requirement</data>
  <data key="d2">Limits of Liability are required in multiple annexes, sub-annexes, and spec items within the solicitation, with narratives demonstrating understanding of their application.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-b1019473eb9ce96e37dbd7a39cfdf02d</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759711346</data>
</node>
<node id="Supply Chain Management">
  <data key="d0">Supply Chain Management</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Supply Chain Management ensures materials, supplies, and equipment availability meet contractual delivery timelines.&lt;SEP&gt;Supply Chain Management ensures availability of materials, supplies, and equipment to meet contractual timelines, as addressed in the technical approach.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-ac133babc8ecde7c6f7014a40f53ce13&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-b1019473eb9ce96e37dbd7a39cfdf02d</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759711346</data>
</node>
<node id="Unit Price Labor">
  <data key="d0">Unit Price Labor</data>
  <data key="d1">requirement</data>
  <data key="d2">Unit Price Labor requires a rate for one hour of work-in-place for work over Limits of Liability and other over-and-above work, encompassing all applicable costs including subcontracted work without post-award renegotiation.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-b1019473eb9ce96e37dbd7a39cfdf02d</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759711346</data>
</node>
<node id="Risk Mitigation">
  <data key="d0">Risk Mitigation</data>
  <data key="d1">requirement</data>
  <data key="d2">Risk Mitigation involves practical contingency plans to address shortages of materials, equipment, and workers to successfully perform the contract.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-b1019473eb9ce96e37dbd7a39cfdf02d</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759711346</data>
</node>
<node id="NAVSTA Mayport">
  <data key="d0">NAVSTA Mayport</data>
  <data key="d1">location</data>
  <data key="d2">NAVSTA Mayport is Naval Station Mayport, featuring facility inventories, site maps, historical work orders, and equipment like weight handling and cross connection control programs.&lt;SEP&gt;NAVSTA Mayport is a naval station that distributes its own electricity and produces and distributes its own water, requiring adequate and sufficient utilities at all times.&lt;SEP&gt;NAVSTA Mayport is a location associated with sub-annexes for facility management, investment, environmental services, and utility distribution of electricity and water.&lt;SEP&gt;NAVSTA Mayport is a naval station with documented programs for weight handling equipment, cross connection control, and storm water pollution prevention.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-516b1e6efecfd543f141d1e1135ec455&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-9e005e41da996ebb18d009a4f87b0e3c&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-ac133babc8ecde7c6f7014a40f53ce13&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-b1019473eb9ce96e37dbd7a39cfdf02d</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759711346</data>
</node>
<node id="MCSF-BI">
  <data key="d0">MCSF-BI</data>
  <data key="d1">organization</data>
  <data key="d2">MCSF-BI is an organization associated with multiple sub-annexes including facility management, custodial, pest control, solid waste management, grounds maintenance, and environmental services.&lt;SEP&gt;MCSF-BI is a location for sub-annexes including facility management, investment, custodial, pest control, waste management, grounds maintenance, and environmental services.&lt;SEP&gt;MCSF-BI is a facility associated with multiple inventory and management documents for systems including cathodic protection, compressed air, lighting, and environmental plans.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-9e005e41da996ebb18d009a4f87b0e3c&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-ac133babc8ecde7c6f7014a40f53ce13&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-b1019473eb9ce96e37dbd7a39cfdf02d</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759711346</data>
</node>
<node id="Maximo">
  <data key="d0">Maximo</data>
  <data key="d1">technology</data>
  <data key="d2">Maximo is a data system critical for maintaining Service Provider, Asset, Specification, and Characteristic Meter Reading data fields throughout the Performance Work Statement.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-b1019473eb9ce96e37dbd7a39cfdf02d</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759711346</data>
</node>
<node id="Annex 6 Port Operations">
  <data key="d0">Annex 6 Port Operations</data>
  <data key="d1">section</data>
  <data key="d2">Annex 6 Port Operations is a section addressing performance methodology for port operations.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-b1019473eb9ce96e37dbd7a39cfdf02d</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759711346</data>
</node>
<node id="Annex 15 Facilities Support">
  <data key="d0">Annex 15 Facilities Support</data>
  <data key="d1">section</data>
  <data key="d2">Annex 15 Facilities Support is a section covering facilities support including facility management, investment, custodial, pest control, solid waste management, training pools, grounds maintenance, and landscaping.&lt;SEP&gt;Annex 15 Facilities Support covers facility-related services including management, investment, custodial, pest control, waste management, training pools, and grounds maintenance for NAVSTA and MCSF-BI.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-ac133babc8ecde7c6f7014a40f53ce13&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-b1019473eb9ce96e37dbd7a39cfdf02d</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759711346</data>
</node>
<node id="Annex 16 Utilities">
  <data key="d0">Annex 16 Utilities</data>
  <data key="d1">section</data>
  <data key="d2">Annex 16 Utilities is a section including utilities management, electrical, and water sub-annexes.&lt;SEP&gt;Annex 16 Utilities includes management, electrical, and water sub-annexes, with specific understanding required for NAVSTA Mayport's self-distribution.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-ac133babc8ecde7c6f7014a40f53ce13&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-b1019473eb9ce96e37dbd7a39cfdf02d</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759711346</data>
</node>
<node id="Annex 17 Transportation">
  <data key="d0">Annex 17 Transportation</data>
  <data key="d1">section</data>
  <data key="d2">Annex 17 Transportation is a section addressing transportation equipment maintenance and repair within specified time frames.&lt;SEP&gt;Annex 17 Transportation is a technical annex for which performance methodology must be detailed in the technical approach.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-ac133babc8ecde7c6f7014a40f53ce13&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-b1019473eb9ce96e37dbd7a39cfdf02d</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759711346</data>
</node>
<node id="Annex 18 Environmental">
  <data key="d0">Annex 18 Environmental</data>
  <data key="d1">section</data>
  <data key="d2">Annex 18 Environmental is a section with sub-annexes for NAVSTA and MCSF-BI addressing environmental requirements.&lt;SEP&gt;Annex 18 Environmental includes sub-annexes for NAVSTA and MCSF-BI, requiring approach description in technical approach.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-ac133babc8ecde7c6f7014a40f53ce13&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-b1019473eb9ce96e37dbd7a39cfdf02d</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759711346</data>
</node>
<node id="Performance Work Statement">
  <data key="d0">Performance Work Statement</data>
  <data key="d1">document</data>
  <data key="d2">The Performance Work Statement details the requirements for Base Operations Support services, including labor, supervision, and equipment necessary for various tasks at the facilities.&lt;SEP&gt;The Performance Work Statement specifies requirements for recurring base operations support services and references all applicable attachments.&lt;SEP&gt;Performance Work Statement outlines requirements for maintenance of data fields in Maximo and other contractual obligations.&lt;SEP&gt;The Performance Work Statement outlines requirements for base operations support services, including specific annexes like Port Operations and Facility Investment.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-3e097b0647fa14f34c4ff76380ed4beb&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-f8cbd3bc2ef4445a2ce77064100a7a3e&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-9775b66c35e6cfe40c05dbf72803d6cd&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-b1019473eb9ce96e37dbd7a39cfdf02d</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759711346</data>
</node>
<node id="Factor 3">
  <data key="d0">Factor 3</data>
  <data key="d1">evaluation_factor</data>
  <data key="d2">Factor 3 evaluates the offeror's technical approach including staffing levels, methodology for performance objectives, systems approach, limits of liability, supply chain management, and risk mitigation.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-b1019473eb9ce96e37dbd7a39cfdf02d</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759711346</data>
</node>
<node id="Factor 4 Small Business Utilization and Participation">
  <data key="d0">Factor 4 Small Business Utilization and Participation</data>
  <data key="d1">evaluation_factor</data>
  <data key="d2">Factor 4 assesses historical small business utilization and proposed participation commitment, requiring at least 20% small business participation of total contract value.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-b1019473eb9ce96e37dbd7a39cfdf02d</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759711346</data>
</node>
<node id="Factor 5 Safety">
  <data key="d0">Factor 5 Safety</data>
  <data key="d1">evaluation_factor</data>
  <data key="d2">Factor 5 evaluates safety through DART Rate, TCR Rate, and a technical approach to Safety Management System implementation.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-b1019473eb9ce96e37dbd7a39cfdf02d</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759711346</data>
</node>
<node id="DART Rate">
  <data key="d0">DART Rate</data>
  <data key="d1">evaluation_factor</data>
  <data key="d2">DART Rate is calculated by multiplying the number of DART incidents by 200,000 and dividing by total employee labor hours, used to evaluate safety trends over five years with defined risk levels.&lt;SEP&gt;DART Rate measures injuries or illnesses resulting in days away from work, restricted duty, or job transfer, calculated for five calendar years using specified formula.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-6277b393cb9cf1d4f0f247c35b0fffa1&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-b1019473eb9ce96e37dbd7a39cfdf02d</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759711346</data>
</node>
<node id="TCR Rate">
  <data key="d0">TCR Rate</data>
  <data key="d1">evaluation_factor</data>
  <data key="d2">TCR Rate is calculated by multiplying the number of TCR incidents by 200,000 and dividing by total employee labor hours, requiring submission of five previous calendar years' data with explanations for trends.&lt;SEP&gt;TCR Rate measures total recordable cases including death, days away, restricted work, medical treatment beyond first aid, or loss of consciousness, calculated for five calendar years using specified formula.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-6277b393cb9cf1d4f0f247c35b0fffa1&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-b1019473eb9ce96e37dbd7a39cfdf02d</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759711346</data>
</node>
<node id="Safety Management System">
  <data key="d0">Safety Management System</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Safety Management System is a framework including management leadership involvement, employee involvement, hazard prevention, hazard control, worksite analysis, and safety training, benchmarked against standards.&lt;SEP&gt;Safety Management System includes management leadership involvement, employee involvement, hazard prevention, hazard control, worksite analysis, and safety training, benchmarked against standards.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-6277b393cb9cf1d4f0f247c35b0fffa1&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-b1019473eb9ce96e37dbd7a39cfdf02d</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759711346</data>
</node>
