<node id="Federal Acquisition Regulation">
  <data key="d0">Federal Acquisition Regulation</data>
  <data key="d1">document</data>
  <data key="d2">The regulation (48 CFR Chapter 1) governing cost principles, clauses, and contract administration, with deviations indicated by "(DEVIATION)".&lt;SEP&gt;Federal Acquisition Regulation (FAR) provides the governing rules for the solicitation, including clauses such as 52.214-7, 52.215-1, 52.232-8, 52.222-43, and 52.222-32.&lt;SEP&gt;Federal Acquisition Regulation (48 CFR Chapter 1) is the source of clauses used in the solicitation or contract, with authorized deviations indicated by "(DEVIATION)" after the clause date.&lt;SEP&gt;The Federal Acquisition Regulation (FAR) is the source of clauses incorporated by reference and in full text within Section I of the contract.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-516b1e6efecfd543f141d1e1135ec455&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-bafeb026eba657c5147474a89dc0e6f9&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-f8cbd3bc2ef4445a2ce77064100a7a3e&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-96e30762ee04dbe2af303802d3d2a936</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759711347</data>
</node>
