  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759711349</data>
</node>
<node id="Government Accountability Office (GAO)">
  <data key="d0">Government Accountability Office (GAO)</data>
  <data key="d1">organization</data>
  <data key="d2">The Government Accountability Office handles protests filed directly with the agency.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-9775b66c35e6cfe40c05dbf72803d6cd</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759711349</data>
</node>
<node id="Jacksonville, FL">
  <data key="d0">Jacksonville, FL</data>
  <data key="d1">location</data>
  <data key="d2">Jacksonville, FL is the location of the NAVFAC SOUTHEAST ACQUISITION CORE office.&lt;SEP&gt;Jacksonville, FL is the city and state for mailing addresses in the solicitation.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-9775b66c35e6cfe40c05dbf72803d6cd&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-4bcb91b404a9ca74c18944c1ba7f80a2</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759711349</data>
</node>
<node id="Solicitation">
  <data key="d0">Solicitation</data>
  <data key="d1">document</data>
  <data key="d2">The Solicitation incorporates FAR and DFARS clauses by reference and full text, and includes evaluation factors.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-9775b66c35e6cfe40c05dbf72803d6cd</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759711349</data>
</node>
<node id="RFP">
  <data key="d0">RFP</data>
  <data key="d1">document</data>
  <data key="d2">The RFP describes performance work statement/specifications for relevant projects in evaluation of corporate experience and past performance.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-9775b66c35e6cfe40c05dbf72803d6cd</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759711349</data>
</node>
<node id="Canadian Commercial Corporation">
  <data key="d0">Canadian Commercial Corporation</data>
  <data key="d1">organization</data>
  <data key="d2">The Canadian Commercial Corporation is exempt from certified cost or pricing data requirements and provides specific data if notified.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-9775b66c35e6cfe40c05dbf72803d6cd</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759711349</data>
</node>
<node id="Public Works and Government Services Canada">
  <data key="d0">Public Works and Government Services Canada</data>
  <data key="d1">organization</data>
  <data key="d2">Public Works and Government Services Canada provides analysis to the Canadian Commercial Corporation for determining fair and reasonable pricing.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-9775b66c35e6cfe40c05dbf72803d6cd</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759711349</data>
</node>
<node id="NAS Jacksonville">
  <data key="d0">NAS Jacksonville</data>
  <data key="d1">location</data>
  <data key="d2">NAS Jacksonville is the location for proposal delivery and site visits in Jacksonville, FL 32212-0030.&lt;SEP&gt;NAS Jacksonville is part of the address for NAVFAC SOUTHEAST ACQUISITION CORE where protests are served.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-9775b66c35e6cfe40c05dbf72803d6cd&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-4bcb91b404a9ca74c18944c1ba7f80a2</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759711349</data>
</node>
<node id="Firm-Fixed Price">
  <data key="d0">Firm-Fixed Price</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Firm-Fixed Price is the contemplated contract type for award resulting from the solicitation.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-9775b66c35e6cfe40c05dbf72803d6cd</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759711349</data>
</node>
<node id="Tradeoff Process">
  <data key="d0">Tradeoff Process</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">The Tradeoff Process is selected for the acquisition to consider award to other than the lowest priced or highest technically rated offeror.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-9775b66c35e6cfe40c05dbf72803d6cd</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759711349</data>
</node>
<node id="Performance Confidence Assessment">
  <data key="d0">Performance Confidence Assessment</data>
  <data key="d1">evaluation_factor</data>
  <data key="d2">The Performance Confidence Assessment rating is part of Factor 6 and is significantly more important than price when combined with technical factors.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-9775b66c35e6cfe40c05dbf72803d6cd</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759711349</data>
</node>
<node id="Basis for Award">
  <data key="d0">Basis for Award</data>
  <data key="d1">section</data>
  <data key="d2">M.1 Basis for Award reserves the right to eliminate offers, negotiate, and award based on best value considering cost/price and other factors.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-9775b66c35e6cfe40c05dbf72803d6cd</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759711349</data>
</node>
<node id="ELIN/Sub-ELIN Prices">
  <data key="d0">ELIN/Sub-ELIN Prices</data>
  <data key="d1">section</data>
  <data key="d2">M.2 ELIN/Sub-ELIN Prices requires rounding unit prices to two decimal places for evaluation.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-9775b66c35e6cfe40c05dbf72803d6cd</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759711349</data>
</node>
<node id="Pricing Discrepancies">
  <data key="d0">Pricing Discrepancies</data>
  <data key="d1">section</data>
  <data key="d2">M.3 Pricing Discrepancies outlines resolution of differences between unit prices and extended totals, prioritizing unit prices.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-9775b66c35e6cfe40c05dbf72803d6cd</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759711349</data>
</node>
<node id="Relevant Project">
  <data key="d0">Relevant Project</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">A Relevant Project demonstrates capability in services similar in size, scope, and complexity to the RFP, with a contract value of at least $15,000,000 per year, either ongoing with 12 months completed or completed within the last five years.&lt;SEP&gt;A Relevant Project demonstrates capability for services similar in size, scope, and complexity to the RFP with a contract value of $15,000,000 or greater, ongoing or completed within five years.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-ac133babc8ecde7c6f7014a40f53ce13&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-9775b66c35e6cfe40c05dbf72803d6cd</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759711349</data>
</node>
<node id="Base Operations Support (BOS)">
  <data key="d0">Base Operations Support (BOS)</data>
  <data key="d1">requirement</data>
  <data key="d2">Base Operations Support (BOS) encompasses services including at least three specific technical annexes and one additional, such as Port Operations, Facility Investment, Electrical, Water, and BSVE.&lt;SEP&gt;Base Operations Support services encompass at least three specific annexes and one other technical annex for relevancy in evaluation.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-ac133babc8ecde7c6f7014a40f53ce13&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-9775b66c35e6cfe40c05dbf72803d6cd</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759711349</data>
</node>
<node id="Port Operations">
  <data key="d0">Port Operations</data>
  <data key="d1">requirement</data>
  <data key="d2">Port Operations (0600000) is a technical annex similar to RFP requirements for relevant project evaluation.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-9775b66c35e6cfe40c05dbf72803d6cd</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759711349</data>
</node>
<node id="Facility Investment">
  <data key="d0">Facility Investment</data>
  <data key="d1">requirement</data>
  <data key="d2">Facility Investment (1502000) includes service orders, HVAC, fire protection, and other items for relevancy evaluation.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-9775b66c35e6cfe40c05dbf72803d6cd</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759711349</data>
</node>
<node id="Electrical">
  <data key="d0">Electrical</data>
  <data key="d1">requirement</data>
  <data key="d2">Electrical (1602000) covers transmission, distribution, operations, maintenance, and repairs similar to RFP requirements.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-9775b66c35e6cfe40c05dbf72803d6cd</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759711349</data>
</node>
<node id="FAR 52.217-5 Evaluation of Options">
  <data key="d0">FAR 52.217-5 Evaluation of Options</data>
  <data key="d1">clause</data>
  <data key="d2">FAR 52.217-5 is included in the solicitation for evaluating all options without obligating their exercise.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-9775b66c35e6cfe40c05dbf72803d6cd</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759711349</data>
</node>
<node id="DFARS 215.304(c)(i)">
  <data key="d0">DFARS 215.304(c)(i)</data>
  <data key="d1">clause</data>
  <data key="d2">DFARS 215.304(c)(i) requires listing small businesses considered in evaluations within the SBSP.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-9775b66c35e6cfe40c05dbf72803d6cd</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759711349</data>
</node>
<node id="Technical Approach to Safety">
  <data key="d0">Technical Approach to Safety</data>
  <data key="d1">requirement</data>
  <data key="d2">Technical Approach to Safety requires a narrative limited to two single-sided pages describing SMS implementation, subcontractor selection, oversight processes, and safety compliance.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-6277b393cb9cf1d4f0f247c35b0fffa1</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759711349</data>
</node>
<node id="Past Performance">
  <data key="d0">Past Performance</data>
  <data key="d1">evaluation_factor</data>
  <data key="d2">Past Performance is evaluated based on recency, relevancy, and quality of recent projects, using CPARS, PPQ, and other sources to assess trends in task completion, deliverables, and cooperation.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-6277b393cb9cf1d4f0f247c35b0fffa1</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759711349</data>
</node>
<node id="Past Performance Questionnaire">
  <data key="d0">Past Performance Questionnaire</data>
  <data key="d1">document</data>
  <data key="d2">Past Performance Questionnaire is a form provided for clients to evaluate offeror performance when CPARS is unavailable, to be submitted with proposals.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-6277b393cb9cf1d4f0f247c35b0fffa1</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759711349</data>
</node>
<node id="Federal Awardee Performance and Integrity Information System">
  <data key="d0">Federal Awardee Performance and Integrity Information System</data>
  <data key="d1">other</data>
  <data key="d2">Federal Awardee Performance and Integrity Information System is a database used by the Government to obtain past performance information.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-6277b393cb9cf1d4f0f247c35b0fffa1</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759711349</data>
</node>
<node id="Electronic Subcontract Reporting System">
  <data key="d0">Electronic Subcontract Reporting System</data>
  <data key="d1">other</data>
  <data key="d2">Electronic Subcontract Reporting System is a source for past performance data reviewed by the Government.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-6277b393cb9cf1d4f0f247c35b0fffa1</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759711349</data>
</node>
<node id="Defense Contract Management Agency">
  <data key="d0">Defense Contract Management Agency</data>
  <data key="d1">organization</data>
  <data key="d2">Defense Contract Management Agency is an entity from which past performance information may be obtained.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-6277b393cb9cf1d4f0f247c35b0fffa1</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759711349</data>
</node>
<node id="52.217-5 Evaluation of Options">
  <data key="d0">52.217-5 Evaluation of Options</data>
  <data key="d1">clause</data>
  <data key="d2">52.217-5 Evaluation of Options is a FAR clause incorporated by reference, effective July 1990.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-6277b393cb9cf1d4f0f247c35b0fffa1</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759711349</data>
</node>
<node id="Very Low Risk">
  <data key="d0">Very Low Risk</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Very Low Risk is defined for DART Rate less than 1.0 and for TCR Rate less than 2.49, indicating strong safety performance.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-6277b393cb9cf1d4f0f247c35b0fffa1</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759711349</data>
</node>
<node id="Low Risk">
  <data key="d0">Low Risk</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Low Risk is defined for DART Rate from 1.0 to 1.99 and for TCR Rate from 2.5 to 3.49.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-6277b393cb9cf1d4f0f247c35b0fffa1</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759711350</data>
</node>
<node id="Moderate Risk">
  <data key="d0">Moderate Risk</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Moderate Risk is defined for DART Rate from 2.0 to 2.99 and for TCR Rate from 3.5 to 4.49, requiring explanations for negative trends.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-6277b393cb9cf1d4f0f247c35b0fffa1</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759711350</data>
</node>
<node id="High Risk">
  <data key="d0">High Risk</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">High Risk is defined for DART Rate from 3.0 to 4.0 and for TCR Rate from 4.5 to 5.99.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-6277b393cb9cf1d4f0f247c35b0fffa1</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759711350</data>
</node>
<node id="Extremely High Risk">
  <data key="d0">Extremely High Risk</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Extremely High Risk is defined for DART Rate greater than 4.0 and for TCR Rate greater than 6.0.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-6277b393cb9cf1d4f0f247c35b0fffa1</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759711350</data>
</node>
<node id="Corporate Experience">
  <data key="d0">Corporate Experience</data>
  <data key="d1">evaluation_factor</data>
  <data key="d2">Corporate Experience is Factor 1, requiring submission of two to five examples of recent relevant projects as prime contractor, assessed for capability to meet solicitation requirements.&lt;SEP&gt;Corporate Experience is Factor 1 of the solicitation, used to identify relevant projects for Past Performance evaluation and determine relevancy based on submitted projects.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-6277b393cb9cf1d4f0f247c35b0fffa1&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-ac133babc8ecde7c6f7014a40f53ce13</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759711350</data>
</node>
<node id="TCR Cases">
  <data key="d0">TCR Cases</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">TCR Cases include injuries or illnesses resulting in death, days away from work, restricted work or transfer to another job beyond the day of injury/illness, medical treatment beyond first aid, or loss of consciousness.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-6277b393cb9cf1d4f0f247c35b0fffa1</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759711350</data>
</node>
<node id="Subcontractor Evaluation Process">
  <data key="d0">Subcontractor Evaluation Process</data>
  <data key="d1">requirement</data>
  <data key="d2">Subcontractor Evaluation Process requires a description of the methodical process used to select potential subcontractors based on safety performance.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-6277b393cb9cf1d4f0f247c35b0fffa1</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759711350</data>
</node>
<node id="Subcontractor Safety Oversight">
  <data key="d0">Subcontractor Safety Oversight</data>
  <data key="d1">requirement</data>
  <data key="d2">Subcontractor Safety Oversight requires a description of processes to oversee safety compliance of subcontractors at all levels, including the offeror's in-house workforce, throughout contract performance.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-6277b393cb9cf1d4f0f247c35b0fffa1</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759711350</data>
</node>
<node id="Evaluation Board">
  <data key="d0">Evaluation Board</data>
  <data key="d1">other</data>
  <data key="d2">Evaluation Board assesses DART and TCR rates, trends, risk levels, and explanations to determine the offeror's history of safe work practices.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-6277b393cb9cf1d4f0f247c35b0fffa1</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759711350</data>
</node>
<node id="Contractor Job-Related Mishap Death">
  <data key="d0">Contractor Job-Related Mishap Death</data>
  <data key="d1">event</data>
  <data key="d2">Contractor Job-Related Mishap Death within the past five years may result in an unacceptable safety factor rating and requires detailed explanation including root cause and corrective actions.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-6277b393cb9cf1d4f0f247c35b0fffa1</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759711350</data>
</node>
<node id="FAR Clauses Incorporated by Reference">
  <data key="d0">FAR Clauses Incorporated by Reference</data>
  <data key="d1">section</data>
  <data key="d2">FAR Clauses Incorporated by Reference is a section listing incorporated Federal Acquisition Regulation clauses, including their numbers, titles, and effective dates.&lt;SEP&gt;FAR Clauses Incorporated by Reference include 52.204-24, 52.209-7, 52.209-13, 52.229-11, with effective dates, in Section K of the solicitation.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-9e005e41da996ebb18d009a4f87b0e3c&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-6277b393cb9cf1d4f0f247c35b0fffa1</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759711350</data>
</node>
<node id="Attachment D">
  <data key="d0">Attachment D</data>
  <data key="d1">document</data>
  <data key="d2">Attachment D is the first page of the Past Performance Questionnaire providing contract and client information for projects when completed PPQs are unavailable.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-6277b393cb9cf1d4f0f247c35b0fffa1</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759711350</data>
</node>
<node id="DART Incidents">
  <data key="d0">DART Incidents</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">DART Incidents are the recordable cases used in the calculation of the DART Rate, submitted for five previous calendar years.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-6277b393cb9cf1d4f0f247c35b0fffa1</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759711350</data>
</node>
<node id="Mayport, Fl">
  <data key="d0">Mayport, Fl</data>
  <data key="d1">location</data>
  <data key="d2">Mayport, FL is the location for inspection and acceptance activities, including BLDG 1966 on Bon Homme Richard St, with zip code 32228-0073.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-729293c3f8703afb2cb5e31cb6ff90dd</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759711350</data>
</node>
<node id="Naval Station Mayport Jacksonville">
  <data key="d0">Naval Station Mayport Jacksonville</data>
  <data key="d1">location</data>
  <data key="d2">Naval Station Mayport Jacksonville, Florida is one of the primary places of performance for the work under the solicitation.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-729293c3f8703afb2cb5e31cb6ff90dd</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759711350</data>
</node>
<node id="Dod AAC N46134">
  <data key="d0">Dod AAC N46134</data>
  <data key="d1">requirement</data>
  <data key="d2">Dod AAC N46134 is the Department of Defense Activity Address Code used for the inspection and acceptance location and place of performance.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-729293c3f8703afb2cb5e31cb6ff90dd</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759711350</data>
</node>
<node id="Inspector Of Record Pwd Mayport">
  <data key="d0">Inspector Of Record Pwd Mayport</data>
  <data key="d1">organization</data>
  <data key="d2">Inspector Of Record Pwd Mayport is the designated inspector for the contract, contactable at telephone 904-270-6716.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-729293c3f8703afb2cb5e31cb6ff90dd</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759711350</data>
</node>
<node id="Solicitation N6945025R0003">
  <data key="d0">Solicitation N6945025R0003</data>
  <data key="d1">document</data>
  <data key="d2">Solicitation N6945025R0003 is the contract solicitation document that includes sections on inspection, acceptance, and deliverables.&lt;SEP&gt;Solicitation N6945025R0003 is a sealed bid solicitation for Base Operations Support services under full and open competition, using NAICS code 561210.&lt;SEP&gt;Solicitation N6945025R0003 is a request for proposals outlining requirements for base operations support services, including evaluation factors and submittal requirements.&lt;SEP&gt;Solicitation N6945025R0003 is a government procurement document for facilities support services, including provided attachment files and Section K representations.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-9e005e41da996ebb18d009a4f87b0e3c&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-f8cbd3bc2ef4445a2ce77064100a7a3e&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-ac133babc8ecde7c6f7014a40f53ce13&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-729293c3f8703afb2cb5e31cb6ff90dd</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759711350</data>
</node>
<node id="N6945025R0003 Sectionf.Pdf">
  <data key="d0">N6945025R0003 Sectionf.Pdf</data>
  <data key="d1">document</data>
  <data key="d2">N6945025R0003 Sectionf.Pdf is the attachment file for Section F deliverables, available on the SAM website at https://sam.gov/.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-729293c3f8703afb2cb5e31cb6ff90dd</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759711350</data>
</node>
<node id="Contract Term">
  <data key="d0">Contract Term</data>
  <data key="d1">requirement</data>
  <data key="d2">Contract Term specifies an initial one-year performance period starting 01 January 2027, with potential extension up to eight years including seven one-year options, and possible further extensions under FAR 52.217-8 and FAR 52.217-9.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-729293c3f8703afb2cb5e31cb6ff90dd</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759711350</data>
</node>
<node id="Transition Period">
  <data key="d0">Transition Period</data>
  <data key="d1">requirement</data>
  <data key="d2">Transition Period allows 90 days for mobilization post-award by 30 September 2026 and demobilization 90 days prior to contract completion to support the follow-on contractor.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-729293c3f8703afb2cb5e31cb6ff90dd</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759711350</data>
</node>
<node id="Pre-Performance Conference">
  <data key="d0">Pre-Performance Conference</data>
  <data key="d1">event</data>
  <data key="d2">Pre-Performance Conference is scheduled within 30 days of contract award to discuss scheduling and administration with the Contracting Officer.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-729293c3f8703afb2cb5e31cb6ff90dd</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759711350</data>
</node>
<node id="Deliverables">
  <data key="d0">Deliverables</data>
  <data key="d1">deliverable</data>
  <data key="d2">Deliverables include files submitted electronically in Microsoft Office 365 compatible format via email or CD-ROM to points of contact in Section F attachment.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-729293c3f8703afb2cb5e31cb6ff90dd</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759711350</data>
</node>
<node id="Line Item 0001">
  <data key="d0">Line Item 0001</data>
  <data key="d1">deliverable</data>
  <data key="d2">Line Item 0001 has a delivery period from 01 Jan 2027 to 31 Dec 2027, quantity 1 each, at the place of performance with DoDAAC N46134.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-729293c3f8703afb2cb5e31cb6ff90dd</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759711350</data>
</node>
<node id="Option Line Item 0003">
  <data key="d0">Option Line Item 0003</data>
  <data key="d1">deliverable</data>
  <data key="d2">Option Line Item 0003 has a delivery period from 01 Jan 2028 to 31 Dec 2028, quantity 1 each, at the place of performance with DoDAAC N46134.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-729293c3f8703afb2cb5e31cb6ff90dd</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759711350</data>
</node>
<node id="Option Line Item 0007">
  <data key="d0">Option Line Item 0007</data>
  <data key="d1">deliverable</data>
  <data key="d2">Option Line Item 0007 has a delivery period from 01 Jan 2029 to 31 Dec 2029, quantity 1 each, at the place of performance with DoDAAC N46134.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-729293c3f8703afb2cb5e31cb6ff90dd</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759711350</data>
</node>
<node id="Inspection And Acceptance Location">
  <data key="d0">Inspection And Acceptance Location</data>
  <data key="d1">requirement</data>
  <data key="d2">Inspection And Acceptance Location is designated as both origin and destination, with instructions in Section F, using DoDAAC N46134 in USA at Navfac Southeast Pwd Mayport.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-729293c3f8703afb2cb5e31cb6ff90dd</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759711350</data>
</node>
<node id="Far 52.217-9">
  <data key="d0">Far 52.217-9</data>
  <data key="d1">clause</data>
  <data key="d2">Far 52.217-9 is the clause titled Option to Extend the Term of the Contract, incorporated into the resulting contract to allow the Government to extend the term.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-729293c3f8703afb2cb5e31cb6ff90dd</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759711350</data>
</node>
<node id="Far 52.217-8">
  <data key="d0">Far 52.217-8</data>
  <data key="d1">clause</data>
  <data key="d2">Far 52.217-8 is the clause titled Option to Extend Services, providing regulatory authority to extend contract performance up to an additional six months beyond the established term.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-729293c3f8703afb2cb5e31cb6ff90dd</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759711350</data>
</node>
<node id="Microsoft Office 365">
  <data key="d0">Microsoft Office 365</data>
  <data key="d1">technology</data>
  <data key="d2">Microsoft Office 365 is the most recent Government-installed version required for compatibility with deliverable file documents submitted electronically.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-729293c3f8703afb2cb5e31cb6ff90dd</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759711350</data>
</node>
<node id="Sam.Gov">
  <data key="d0">Sam.Gov</data>
  <data key="d1">technology</data>
  <data key="d2">Sam.Gov is the website where the files for Section F are provided as attachments, accessible at https://sam.gov/.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-729293c3f8703afb2cb5e31cb6ff90dd</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759711350</data>
</node>
<node id="Cd-Rom">
  <data key="d0">Cd-Rom</data>
  <data key="d1">technology</data>
  <data key="d2">Cd-Rom is the medium for submitting deliverables if email attachment file size is exceeded.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-729293c3f8703afb2cb5e31cb6ff90dd</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759711350</data>
</node>
<node id="Option Periods">
  <data key="d0">Option Periods</data>
  <data key="d1">requirement</data>
  <data key="d2">Option Periods consist of seven one-year periods, each 12 months, exercisable by the Government, with the entire contract duration potentially reaching eight years if all are exercised.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-729293c3f8703afb2cb5e31cb6ff90dd</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759711350</data>
</node>
