  <data key="d1">clause</data>
  <data key="d2">FAR 15.404-1 is a federal acquisition regulation clause guiding appropriate methodologies for price evaluation by the Contracting Officer.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-ac133babc8ecde7c6f7014a40f53ce13</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759711353</data>
</node>
<node id="Unbalanced Pricing">
  <data key="d0">Unbalanced Pricing</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Unbalanced Pricing refers to pricing where line items are significantly overstated or understated, potentially representing an unacceptable risk to the government.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-ac133babc8ecde7c6f7014a40f53ce13</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759711353</data>
</node>
