  <data key="d0">52.217-8 Option to Extend Services</data>
  <data key="d1">clause</data>
  <data key="d2">The Government may require continued performance of any services within the limits and at the rates specified in the contract, adjustable only for revisions to prevailing labor rates provided by the Secretary of Labor, with the option exercisable more than once but total extension not exceeding 6 months, exercised by written notice to the Contractor prior to contract expiration.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-bafeb026eba657c5147474a89dc0e6f9</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759711354</data>
</node>
<node id="52.217-9 Option to Extend the Term of the Contract">
  <data key="d0">52.217-9 Option to Extend the Term of the Contract</data>
  <data key="d1">clause</data>
  <data key="d2">The Government may extend the term of the contract by written notice to the Contractor prior to completion of the current period, provided preliminary written notice of intent is given at least 30 days before contract performance expires, with the extended contract including this option clause and total duration not exceeding 96 months.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-bafeb026eba657c5147474a89dc0e6f9</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759711354</data>
</node>
<node id="52.219-4 Notice of Price Evaluation Preference for HUBZone Small Business Concerns">
  <data key="d0">52.219-4 Notice of Price Evaluation Preference for HUBZone Small Business Concerns</data>
  <data key="d1">clause</data>
  <data key="d2">Offers are evaluated by adding a 10 percent factor to prices except for HUBZone small business concerns that have not waived the preference and otherwise successful small business concerns, applied on a line item basis before other evaluation factors, with award to HUBZone small business concerns in ties with large businesses, and provisions for waiver and joint venture work requirements.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-bafeb026eba657c5147474a89dc0e6f9</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759711354</data>
</node>
<node id="52.219-28 Postaward Small Business Program Rerepresentation">
  <data key="d0">52.219-28 Postaward Small Business Program Rerepresentation</data>
  <data key="d1">clause</data>
  <data key="d2">The Contractor must rerepresent its size and socioeconomic status upon events like novation, merger, acquisition, or specified intervals for long-term contracts and orders, using SAM or specific forms if no SAM representation, covering categories like small business, HUBZone, women-owned, veteran-owned, with joint venture requirements.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-bafeb026eba657c5147474a89dc0e6f9</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759711354</data>
</node>
<node id="52.222-42 Statement of Equivalent Rates for Federal Hires">
  <data key="d0">52.222-42 Statement of Equivalent Rates for Federal Hires</data>
  <data key="d1">clause</data>
  <data key="d2">Identifies classes of service employees expected under the contract and states equivalent wages and fringe benefits if employed by the contracting agency under 5 U.S.C. 5341 or 5332, for information only and not a wage determination, listing classes like Boiler Tender, Carpenter Maintenance, Electrician Maintenance.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-bafeb026eba657c5147474a89dc0e6f9</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759711354</data>
</node>
<node id="52.242-4 Certification of Final Indirect Costs">
  <data key="d0">52.242-4 Certification of Final Indirect Costs</data>
  <data key="d1">clause</data>
  <data key="d2">The Contractor must certify proposals to establish or modify final indirect cost rates using a specified format signed by a vice president or chief financial officer level, with failure resulting in unilateral rates by the Contracting Officer, certifying allowability under FAR cost principles.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-bafeb026eba657c5147474a89dc0e6f9</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759711354</data>
</node>
<node id="52.252-2 Clauses Incorporated by Reference">
  <data key="d0">52.252-2 Clauses Incorporated by Reference</data>
  <data key="d1">clause</data>
  <data key="d2">Incorporates clauses by reference with same force as full text, available upon request from the Contracting Officer or electronically at specified addresses including acquisition.gov, farsite.hill.af.mil, and secnav.navy.mil.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-bafeb026eba657c5147474a89dc0e6f9</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759711354</data>
</node>
<node id="52.252-4 Alterations in Contract">
  <data key="d0">52.252-4 Alterations in Contract</data>
  <data key="d1">clause</data>
  <data key="d2">Specifies portions of the contract that are altered as indicated.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-bafeb026eba657c5147474a89dc0e6f9</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759711354</data>
</node>
<node id="52.252-6 Authorized Deviations in Clauses">
  <data key="d0">52.252-6 Authorized Deviations in Clauses</data>
  <data key="d1">clause</data>
  <data key="d2">Indicates use of FAR or DFARS clauses with authorized deviations by adding "(DEVIATION)" after the clause date or regulation name.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-bafeb026eba657c5147474a89dc0e6f9</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759711354</data>
</node>
<node id="252.232-7007 Limitation of Government's Obligation">
  <data key="d0">252.232-7007 Limitation of Government's Obligation</data>
  <data key="d1">clause</data>
  <data key="d2">Specifies incrementally funded contract line items with allotted amounts available for payment, requiring the Contractor to perform up to the point of total payable amount by the Government including reimbursement.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-bafeb026eba657c5147474a89dc0e6f9</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759711354</data>
</node>
<node id="HUBZone Small Business Concern">
  <data key="d0">HUBZone Small Business Concern</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">A small business concern qualified under 13 CFR part 126, eligible for price evaluation preference unless waived, with joint ventures requiring at least 40 percent aggregate work by HUBZone parties beyond administrative functions.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-bafeb026eba657c5147474a89dc0e6f9</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759711355</data>
</node>
<node id="Small Business Concern">
  <data key="d0">Small Business Concern</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">A concern independently owned and operated, not dominant in its field, qualified as small under 13 CFR part 121 and size standards, including affiliates determined by factors like common ownership and management.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-bafeb026eba657c5147474a89dc0e6f9</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759711355</data>
</node>
<node id="Long-term Contract">
  <data key="d0">Long-term Contract</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">A contract of more than five years in duration including options, excluding those extended cumulatively not exceeding six months under 52.217-8 or similar authority.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-bafeb026eba657c5147474a89dc0e6f9</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759711355</data>
</node>
<node id="Secretary of Labor">
  <data key="d0">Secretary of Labor</data>
  <data key="d1">person</data>
  <data key="d2">Provides revisions to prevailing labor rates for adjusting rates in service extensions.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-bafeb026eba657c5147474a89dc0e6f9</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759711355</data>
</node>
<node id="Defense Federal Acquisition Supplement">
  <data key="d0">Defense Federal Acquisition Supplement</data>
  <data key="d1">document</data>
  <data key="d2">The supplement (48 CFR Chapter 2) with clauses incorporated, deviations indicated by "(DEVIATION)".</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-bafeb026eba657c5147474a89dc0e6f9</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759711355</data>
</node>
<node id="North American Industry Classification System">
  <data key="d0">North American Industry Classification System</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">The classification system (NAICS) with codes assigned to the contract, corresponding to size standards for small business qualification.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-bafeb026eba657c5147474a89dc0e6f9</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759711355</data>
</node>
<node id="Evaluation Preference">
  <data key="d0">Evaluation Preference</data>
  <data key="d1">evaluation_factor</data>
  <data key="d2">A 10 percent factor added to offer prices for evaluation, except for non-waived HUBZone small business concerns and certain small business offers, applied before other factors on a line item or group basis.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-bafeb026eba657c5147474a89dc0e6f9</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759711355</data>
</node>
<node id="52.216-18 Ordering">
  <data key="d0">52.216-18 Ordering</data>
  <data key="d1">clause</data>
  <data key="d2">Specifies that any order issued during the effective period of the contract but not completed within that period must be completed by the Contractor within the time specified in the order, with the contract governing rights and obligations as if completed during the effective period, and no deliveries required after the contract completion date or final task order completion date, whichever is later.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-bafeb026eba657c5147474a89dc0e6f9</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759711355</data>
</node>
<node id="52.219-28 Postaward Small Business Program Rerepresentation (Alternate I)">
  <data key="d0">52.219-28 Postaward Small Business Program Rerepresentation (Alternate I)</data>
  <data key="d1">clause</data>
  <data key="d2">As prescribed in 19.309(c)(2), substitutes paragraph (h)(1) of the basic clause to require the Contractor to represent its small business size status for each NAICS code assigned to the contract, with an example provided for NAICS Code 561210 and size standard of $47,000,000.00.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-bafeb026eba657c5147474a89dc0e6f9</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759711355</data>
</node>
<node id="Novation Agreement">
  <data key="d0">Novation Agreement</data>
  <data key="d1">document</data>
  <data key="d2">An agreement executed to transfer contract rights and obligations to a new party, triggering rerepresentation of size and socioeconomic status within 30 days under 52.219-28.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-bafeb026eba657c5147474a89dc0e6f9</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759711355</data>
</node>
<node id="Merger">
  <data key="d0">Merger</data>
  <data key="d1">event</data>
  <data key="d2">A business merger that does not require a novation, triggering rerepresentation of size and socioeconomic status within 30 days under 52.219-28.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-bafeb026eba657c5147474a89dc0e6f9</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759711355</data>
</node>
<node id="Acquisition">
  <data key="d0">Acquisition</data>
  <data key="d1">event</data>
  <data key="d2">A business acquisition that does not require a novation, triggering rerepresentation of size and socioeconomic status within 30 days under 52.219-28.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-bafeb026eba657c5147474a89dc0e6f9</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759711355</data>
</node>
<node id="List of Qualified HUBZone Small Business Concerns">
  <data key="d0">List of Qualified HUBZone Small Business Concerns</data>
  <data key="d1">document</data>
  <data key="d2">The official list maintained by the Small Business Administration of certified HUBZone small business concerns, used for representation accuracy under 13 CFR part 126 and 52.219-28.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-bafeb026eba657c5147474a89dc0e6f9</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759711355</data>
</node>
<node id="29 CFR Part 4">
  <data key="d0">29 CFR Part 4</data>
  <data key="d1">document</data>
  <data key="d2">The regulations of the Secretary of Labor implementing the Service Contract Labor Standards, referenced in 52.222-42 for equivalent rates.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-bafeb026eba657c5147474a89dc0e6f9</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759711355</data>
</node>
<node id="5 U.S.C. 5341">
  <data key="d0">5 U.S.C. 5341</data>
  <data key="d1">document</data>
  <data key="d2">The United States Code provision on prevailing rate systems for federal employees, referenced in 52.222-42 for determining equivalent wages and fringe benefits.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-bafeb026eba657c5147474a89dc0e6f9</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759711355</data>
</node>
<node id="NAICS Code 561210">
  <data key="d0">NAICS Code 561210</data>
  <data key="d1">section</data>
  <data key="d2">The North American Industry Classification System code for facilities support services, with a small business size standard of $47,000,000.00 as exemplified in 52.219-28 Alternate I.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-bafeb026eba657c5147474a89dc0e6f9</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759711355</data>
</node>
<node id="Certificate of Final Indirect Costs">
  <data key="d0">Certificate of Final Indirect Costs</data>
  <data key="d1">document</data>
  <data key="d2">The certification format required under 52.242-4 for proposals to establish or modify final indirect cost rates, attesting to allowability under FAR cost principles, signed by a senior official.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-bafeb026eba657c5147474a89dc0e6f9</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759711355</data>
</node>
<node id="Federal Supply Schedule">
  <data key="d0">Federal Supply Schedule</data>
  <data key="d1">document</data>
  <data key="d2">A multiple-award contract under FAR subpart 8.4 for issuing orders, where certain rerepresentation requirements under 52.219-28 do not apply.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-bafeb026eba657c5147474a89dc0e6f9</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759711355</data>
</node>
<node id="NAVFAC SE Contracting Officer">
  <data key="d0">NAVFAC SE Contracting Officer</data>
  <data key="d1">person</data>
  <data key="d2">The NAVFAC SE Contracting Officer provides written approval required for the contract to be binding.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-96e30762ee04dbe2af303802d3d2a936</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759711355</data>
</node>
<node id="Liquidated Damages">
  <data key="d0">Liquidated Damages</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Liquidated damages compensate the Government for administrative costs and other expenses resulting from the Contractor's nonperformed or unsatisfactory performance, calculated per Section H.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-96e30762ee04dbe2af303802d3d2a936</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759711355</data>
</node>
<node id="Section I - Contract Clauses">
  <data key="d0">Section I - Contract Clauses</data>
  <data key="d1">section</data>
  <data key="d2">Section I lists FAR clauses and DFARS clauses incorporated by reference and includes full text of specific clauses applicable to the contract.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-96e30762ee04dbe2af303802d3d2a936</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759711355</data>
</node>
<node id="FAR Clauses Incorporated By Reference">
  <data key="d0">FAR Clauses Incorporated By Reference</data>
  <data key="d1">section</data>
  <data key="d2">This section within Section I lists numerous FAR clauses by number, title, and effective date, incorporated into the contract by reference.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-96e30762ee04dbe2af303802d3d2a936</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759711355</data>
</node>
<node id="DFARS Clauses Incorporated By Reference">
  <data key="d0">DFARS Clauses Incorporated By Reference</data>
  <data key="d1">section</data>
  <data key="d2">This section within Section I lists numerous DFARS clauses by number, title, and effective date, incorporated into the contract by reference.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-96e30762ee04dbe2af303802d3d2a936</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759711355</data>
</node>
<node id="FAR 52.204-1 Approval Of Contract">
  <data key="d0">FAR 52.204-1 Approval Of Contract</data>
  <data key="d1">clause</data>
  <data key="d2">This FAR clause states that the contract is subject to written approval by the NAVFAC SE Contracting Officer and is not binding until approved.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-96e30762ee04dbe2af303802d3d2a936</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759711355</data>
</node>
<node id="FAR 52.211-11 Liquidated Damages-Supplies Services Or Research And Development">
  <data key="d0">FAR 52.211-11 Liquidated Damages-Supplies Services Or Research And Development</data>
  <data key="d1">clause</data>
  <data key="d2">This FAR clause specifies that the Contractor pays liquidated damages of $ per calendar day of delay for failure to deliver supplies or perform services within the specified time, with liability continuing upon termination.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-96e30762ee04dbe2af303802d3d2a936</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759711355</data>
</node>
<node id="FAR 52.215-21 Requirements For Certified Cost Or Pricing Data And Data Other Than Certified Cost Or Pricing Data-Modifications Alternate I">
  <data key="d0">FAR 52.215-21 Requirements For Certified Cost Or Pricing Data And Data Other Than Certified Cost Or Pricing Data-Modifications Alternate I</data>
  <data key="d1">clause</data>
  <data key="d2">This alternate I version of the FAR clause requires the Contractor to submit certified cost or pricing data and supporting attachments in a format designated as TBD.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-96e30762ee04dbe2af303802d3d2a936</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759711355</data>
</node>
<node id="FAR 52.215-21 Requirements For Certified Cost Or Pricing Data And Data Other Than Certified Cost Or Pricing Data-Modifications Alternate III">
  <data key="d0">FAR 52.215-21 Requirements For Certified Cost Or Pricing Data And Data Other Than Certified Cost Or Pricing Data-Modifications Alternate III</data>
  <data key="d1">clause</data>
  <data key="d2">This alternate III version of the FAR clause requires the Contractor to submit the cost portion of the proposal via electronic media specified as CD.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-96e30762ee04dbe2af303802d3d2a936</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759711355</data>
</node>
<node id="FAR 52.216-18 Ordering">
  <data key="d0">FAR 52.216-18 Ordering</data>
  <data key="d1">clause</data>
  <data key="d2">This FAR clause governs the issuance of delivery orders or task orders for supplies and services under the contract, including methods such as mail, fax, or electronic transmission.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-96e30762ee04dbe2af303802d3d2a936</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759711355</data>
</node>
<node id="FAR 52.216-19 Order Limitations">
  <data key="d0">FAR 52.216-19 Order Limitations</data>
  <data key="d1">clause</data>
  <data key="d2">This FAR clause sets a minimum order amount of $2,500.00, maximum single item order of $250,000.00, and maximum combination order of $1,000,000.00 excluding certain task orders, with provisions for honoring excess orders under conditions.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-96e30762ee04dbe2af303802d3d2a936</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759711355</data>
</node>
<node id="FAR 52.216-22 Indefinite Quantity">
  <data key="d0">FAR 52.216-22 Indefinite Quantity</data>
  <data key="d1">clause</data>
  <data key="d2">This FAR clause establishes the contract as an indefinite-quantity contract with estimated quantities in the Schedule, requiring the Government to order at least the minimum and up to the maximum quantity via orders.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-96e30762ee04dbe2af303802d3d2a936</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759711355</data>
</node>
<node id="FAR 52.217-8 Option To Extend Services">
  <data key="d0">FAR 52.217-8 Option To Extend Services</data>
  <data key="d1">clause</data>
  <data key="d2">This FAR clause allows the Government to require continued performance of services for up to 6 months total, at rates specified in the contract, adjustable only for labor rate revisions, exercisable by written notice prior to expiration.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-96e30762ee04dbe2af303802d3d2a936</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759711355</data>
</node>
<node id="FAR 52.217-9 Option To Extend The Term Of The Contract">
  <data key="d0">FAR 52.217-9 Option To Extend The Term Of The Contract</data>
  <data key="d1">clause</data>
  <data key="d2">This FAR clause permits the Government to extend the contract term by written notice, with preliminary notice 30 days before expiration, for a total duration not exceeding 96 months including options.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-96e30762ee04dbe2af303802d3d2a936</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759711355</data>
</node>
<node id="FAR 52.219-4 Notice Of Price Evaluation Preference For Hubzone Small Business Concerns">
  <data key="d0">FAR 52.219-4 Notice Of Price Evaluation Preference For Hubzone Small Business Concerns</data>
  <data key="d1">clause</data>
  <data key="d2">This FAR clause provides an evaluation preference by adding 10 percent to the price of offers except those from HUBZone small business concerns that have not waived the preference.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-96e30762ee04dbe2af303802d3d2a936</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759711355</data>
</node>
<node id="Kaspersky Lab">
  <data key="d0">Kaspersky Lab</data>
  <data key="d1">organization</data>
  <data key="d2">Kaspersky Lab is a covered entity whose hardware, software, and services are prohibited from government contracting under FAR 52.204-23.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-96e30762ee04dbe2af303802d3d2a936</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759711355</data>
</node>
<node id="ByteDance">
  <data key="d0">ByteDance</data>
  <data key="d1">organization</data>
  <data key="d2">ByteDance is associated with covered applications prohibited from government use under FAR 52.204-27.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-96e30762ee04dbe2af303802d3d2a936</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759711355</data>
</node>
<node id="NIST SP 800-171">
  <data key="d0">NIST SP 800-171</data>
  <data key="d1">document</data>
